**Q1. Differentiate between `ArrayList` and `LinkedList` in Java. (3 Marks)**

**Model Answer:**

| Feature | `ArrayList` | `LinkedList` |
|---|---|---|
| Internal structure | Resizable **dynamic array** | **Doubly-linked** list of nodes |
| Random access (`get(i)`) | $O(1)$ — direct indexing | $O(n)$ — must traverse from head |
| Insertion/Deletion at ends | Amortized $O(1)$ | $O(1)$ (pointer rewiring) |
| Insertion/Deletion in middle | $O(n)$ — shifts elements | $O(1)$ once position is found |
| Memory overhead | Less (contiguous array) | More (each node stores prev/next pointers) |
| Implements | `List` only | `List` **and** `Deque` (can act as queue/stack) |

Use `ArrayList` when reads dominate; use `LinkedList` when you do many insertions/deletions.

