#### **Question B (14 Marks) – Alternative Choice**

**(a)** Explain the `Map` interface in Java. Compare `HashMap`, `TreeMap`, and `Hashtable` with respect to ordering, thread-safety, and null handling. **(7 Marks)**

**Model Solution:**

The `Map<K, V>` interface in `java.util` represents a mapping from keys to values. It is **not** a part of the `Collection` hierarchy. Each key maps to at most one value.

**Key methods:** `put(K, V)`, `get(Object)`, `remove(Object)`, `containsKey(Object)`, `containsValue(Object)`, `keySet()`, `values()`, `entrySet()`.

**Comparison table:**

| Feature | `HashMap` | `TreeMap` | `Hashtable` |
|---|---|---|---|
| Internal structure | Hash table | Red-Black tree | Synchronized hash table |
| Ordering | None | Sorted by keys (natural / Comparator) | None |
| Time complexity | $O(1)$ average | $O(\log n)$ | $O(1)$ but slower due to sync |
| Thread-safe | No | No | Yes (legacy) |
| Allows null key | Yes (one only) | No (throws NPE) | No |
| Allows null value | Yes (multiple) | No | No |
| Iterator type | Fail-fast | Fail-fast | Enumerator (fail-fast by default) |
| Use case | General-purpose cache | Sorted key directory | Legacy multi-threaded code |

**(b)** Write a Java program to count the frequency of each word in a given string using a `HashMap`. **(7 Marks)**

**Model Solution:**

```java
import java.util.*;

public class WordFrequency {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String text = "java is powerful java is platform independent java is secure";
        String[] words = text.toLowerCase().split(" ");

        // HashMap: word -> frequency
        HashMap<String, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();

        for (String word : words) {
            // getOrDefault returns 0 if word not yet present
            freq.put(word, freq.getOrDefault(word, 0) + 1);
        }

        System.out.println("Word frequencies:");
        for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : freq.entrySet()) {
            System.out.println(entry.getKey() + " : " + entry.getValue());
        }
    }
}
```

**Output (order may vary because HashMap is unordered):**
```
Word frequencies:
java : 3
is : 3
powerful : 1
platform : 1
independent : 1
secure : 1
```

