### 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes That Cost Marks:**
> 1. **Forgetting to override `hashCode()`** when overriding `equals()` → silently breaks `HashSet` and `HashMap` (deduplication fails). **Penalty: 1–2 marks.**
> 2. **Using raw types** like `List l = new ArrayList();` instead of `List<String> l = new ArrayList<>();` → loses the "Generics" mark in 14-mark questions.
> 3. **Confusing `Collection` and `Collections`** → `Collection` is an interface; `Collections` is a utility class with static methods like `sort`, `reverse`, `shuffle`. Examiners will deduct at least **1 mark** for this.
> 4. **Claiming `Hashtable` is modern** → It is a **legacy class** synchronized from JDK 1.0. The modern alternative is `ConcurrentHashMap` (not in KTU Module 4 but worth knowing).
> 5. **Mixing up `keySet()` and `entrySet()` iteration** → When you need both key and value, **always use `entrySet()`**; iterating `keySet()` and calling `get(k)` for each is $O(n^2)$ on a `HashMap`.
> 6. **Forgetting that `TreeSet`/`TreeMap` do NOT allow null keys** → results in `NullPointerException` at runtime.

