### 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Final 60-Second Revision Checklist for KTU Module 4:**
> 
> ✅ **Root interfaces**: `Iterable` → `Collection` → (`List`, `Set`, `Queue`). `Map` is a **separate** hierarchy.
> 
> ✅ **`List` is ordered + indexed + allows duplicates.** `Set` has **no duplicates**. `Map` maps **unique keys** to values.
> 
> ✅ **Implementations to memorize:**
>    - List → `ArrayList` (array), `LinkedList` (linked nodes)
>    - Set → `HashSet` (hash), `LinkedHashSet` (hash + insertion order), `TreeSet` (sorted)
>    - Map → `HashMap` (hash), `LinkedHashMap` (hash + order), `TreeMap` (sorted), `Hashtable` (legacy, synchronized)
> 
> ✅ **Time complexity golden rule:** Hash-based = $O(1)$ average; Tree-based = $O(\log n)$; ArrayList get = $O(1)$, insert/remove in middle = $O(n)$.
> 
> ✅ **Use Generics** (`List<String>`) always — never raw types in 2024-scheme answers.
> 
> ✅ **`Comparable` vs `Comparator`:** `Comparable` = inside the class (`compareTo`, natural order, one per class). `Comparator` = outside the class (`compare`, custom, multiple allowed).
> 
> ✅ **Hash contract:** If `a.equals(b)` then `a.hashCode() == b.hashCode()`. **Always override both together.**
> 
> ✅ **`Map` is not a `Collection`** — this is a KTU 2-mark "favourite".
> 
> ✅ **Iteration choices:** enhanced for-loop, `Iterator` (fail-fast, supports `remove()`), `ListIterator` (bidirectional, list-only).
> 
> ✅ **`Collections` (utility class) vs `Collection` (interface)** — different things!
> 
> ✅ **`HashSet` uses `HashMap` internally**; `TreeSet` uses `TreeMap` internally — this is often asked as a 3-mark "explain the internal working" question.

